"government figures show that relative low income was at the same level in 2018/19 as in 2009/10 while absolute low income fell by one percentage point. another measure of poverty, produced by the social metrics commission, does show a fall under this government.",relative poverty has increased since 2009-10 while absolute poverty has declined. but boris johnson has only been pm since july 2019 and we do not have figures to compare since his government began.
